.TH Cfr-Debug 1 "2026-07-11" "coffer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cfr-debug \- headless coffer PTY inspector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cfr-debug
[\fI\,options\/\fR] [\fB\-\-\fR \fI\,command args...\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cfr-debug
spawns a child process on a pseudo-terminal, pipes its output through
coffer, and renders the resulting grid as plain text.
The coffer output callback is wired back to the PTY, so terminal
queries (DA, DSR, kitty keyboard protocol) receive proper replies.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-rows\fR, \fB\-r\fR \fIROWS\fR
Terminal rows (default: 24).
.TP
\fB\-\-cols\fR, \fB\-c\fR \fICOLS\fR
Terminal columns (default: 80).
.TP
\fB\-\-wait\fR, \fB\-w\fR \fISEC\fR
Initial wait in seconds before reading script or rendering (default: 3).
.TP
\fB\-\-script\fR, \fB\-f\fR \fIFILE\fR
Execute commands from a script file. See
.B SCRIPT FILE
below.
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR, \fB\-o\fR \fIFILE\fR
Save raw PTY output to
.IR FILE .
.TP
\fB\-\-show\-row\fR, \fB\-s\fR \fIROW\fR
Dump a specific row (repeatable). When combined with
.BR \-\-quiet ,
only specified rows are shown.
.TP
\fB\-\-cell\-data\fR, \fB\-d\fR
Dump raw cell data (codepoint, width) alongside rendered text.
.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR, \fB\-q\fR
Suppress rendering of rows not selected with
.BR \-\-show\-row .
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\-spec\fR
Emit a machine-readable tab-separated flag listing for downstream tooling.
.SH SCRIPT FILE
When run with
.BR \-\-script ,
each non-blank, non-comment line is parsed as a command:
.TP
.BI "wait " SECONDS
Drain PTY output for
.I SECONDS
seconds (accepts decimals).
.TP
.BI "send " TEXT
Send
.I TEXT
to the PTY. Backslash escapes are expanded:
.B \en
= CR,
.B \er
= CR,
.B \ee
= ESC,
.B \et
= TAB,
.B \e\e
= backslash.
.TP
.BI "raw " "HEX [HEX ...]"
Send literal bytes specified as space-separated hex pairs
(e.g.\&
.BR "raw ff fc 01" ).
.TP
.BI "assert\-contains " TEXT
Fail with exit code 1 if the rendered grid does not contain
.IR TEXT .
.TP
.BI "assert\-not\-contains " TEXT
Fail with exit code 1 if the rendered grid contains
.IR TEXT .
.TP
.B render
Dump the current grid to stdout.
.TP
.BI "# " comment
Lines starting with
.B #
are ignored.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Capture the initial screen of crush:
.EX
cfr-debug \-c 68 \-r 20 \-w 5 \-\- crush
.EE
.TP
Scripted CI test with assertions:
.EX
cfr-debug \-r 24 \-c 80 \-f test.script \-\- sh \-c "echo hello world"
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success; all assertions passed (if any).
.TP
.B 1
An assertion failed, or a runtime error occurred.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TERM
The child process sees
.BR xterm\-256color .
.TP
.B COLORTERM
The child process sees
.BR truecolor .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR coffer (7)
.SH BUGS
No interactive input \(em all input is scripted via
.BR \-\-script .
No mouse support.
